  "body": "New blob type transactions have different network propagation semantics, as outlined here:\n\nhttps://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-4844#networking\n\nBesu should filter out these transactions from being propagated in their entirety; instead only their hashes should be propagated.  Transactions need to then be returned to peers that request it via `GetPooledTransactions`\n\nTest cases to cover:\n- when a new blob arrives in the pool, it's hash is propagated to all peers, not its body.\n- existing test cases which cover `GetPooledTransactions` have variants to ensure they work with blob'd transactions.",
